{"color": "cyan", "emoji": "\ud83d\udee0\ufe0f", "event_type": "Command Finished", "message": "completed, exit 0: /bin/zsh -lc \"sed -n '1,220p' infra/persistence/README.md\"", "raw_event": {"item": {"aggregated_output": "# Persistence Notes\n\nUse this directory for notes about local durable data as infrastructure services are added.\n\nExamples that belong here:\n\n- where Docker volumes store PostgreSQL state in development\n- how the file-backed GCS emulator persists blobs across restarts\n- backup, reset, and cleanup guidance for local persistent data\n\nThis directory is for documentation and conventions, not checked-in database dumps or generated runtime data.\n", "command": "/bin/zsh -lc \"sed -n '1,220p' infra/persistence/README.md\"", "exit_code": 0, "id": "item_17", "status": "completed", "type": "command_execution"}, "type": "item.completed"}, "task_display_context": {"event_number": 38, "prompt_index": 5, "prompt_name": "04 \u2014 Docker Compose Foundation", "prompt_total": 100}, "timestap": "2026-03-31T21:31:51-07:00"}
