{"color": "green", "emoji": "\ud83d\udcac", "event_type": "Agent Message", "message": "Implemented the Docker Compose foundation and checkpointed the code changes in commit `740b370` (`feat(prompt-04): docker compose foundation`). The stack now includes `frontend`, `backend`, `postgres`, and a file-backed `gcs` emulator wi...", "raw_event": {"item": {"id": "item_91", "text": "Implemented the Docker Compose foundation and checkpointed the code changes in commit `740b370` (`feat(prompt-04): docker compose foundation`). The stack now includes `frontend`, `backend`, `postgres`, and a file-backed `gcs` emulator with named persistent volumes, plus the existing browser QA container. I also added minimal backend storage config/health reporting and updated the repo docs for safe `up`, `down`, and `down --volumes` usage.\n\nVerification completed with `./scripts/dev-compose.sh config`, `python -m pytest` in [`backend/`](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend), a full `./scripts/dev-compose.sh up --build -d`, service probes for backend/frontend/GCS/Postgres, volume inspection, and a clean `./scripts/dev-compose.sh down`. The required reviewer summary was written as the final step at [`prompts/04-docker-compose-foundation.summary.md`](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/prompts/04-docker-compose-foundation.summary.md).", "type": "agent_message"}, "type": "item.completed"}, "task_display_context": {"event_number": 165, "prompt_index": 5, "prompt_name": "04 \u2014 Docker Compose Foundation", "prompt_total": 100}, "timestap": "2026-03-31T21:39:28-07:00"}
